OL,3,C'It's taken us 26 years to get here':
OL,4,COmagh bomb inquiry opens
OL,6,FThe chair of the Omagh Bombing Inquiry
OL,7,Fhas vowed it will undertake its work
OL,8,F"rigorously and fearlessly".
OL,10,FScottish judge Lord Turnbull was
OL,11,Fspeaking during the first public
OL,12,Fhearing of the probe into the 1998
OL,13,Fatrocity which claimed 29 lives,
OL,14,Fincluding a woman pregnant with twins.
OL,16,FBereaved families and survivors
OL,17,Fgathered at the Strule Arts Centre in
OL,18,Fthe Co Tyrone town for the hearing in
OL,19,Fthe inquiry which will examine whether
OL,20,Fthe atrocity could reasonably have
OL,21,Fbeen prevented by UK authorities.
